710354f-c.text:
(1)
Ninth Avenue, west side, south from W. 28th Street, showing the easterly side of Chelsea Park. Across same appears the four story factory of Eny-Scheerer and Co.
Beyond is the 10 story structure occupied by Heywood, Strasser and Voight Litho.Co. This is at the S.W. corner of W. 26th Street.
June 28, 1928
P. L. Sperr
(2)
Same as above, looking southward,after demolition of
'E1'. This is a closer view.
P. L. Sperr  April 18, 1941
(3)
9th Avenue, north side, between 26th and 27th, same as
two preceding views from a different angle.
P. L Sperr  April 18, 1941
